{
  "name": "Turkish Red Lentil Soup with Mint",
  "instructions": "1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add onion and sauté until beginning to soften, about 2 minutes. Stir in garlic and cook for additional 2 minutes.\n\n2. Add diced tomatoes and cook for 10 minutes. Stir in chicken stock, lentils, bulgur, rice, tomato paste, mint, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until lentils and rice are tender, about 30 minutes.\n\n3. Puree soup with an immersion blender until smooth. Serve with additional mint and lemon wedges if desired.",
